items.title: SCOTUS allows Lisa Cook to stay on Fed into 2026
items.description: The Supreme Court moved to allow Lisa Cook to remain on the central bank board.

items.title: Senate to vote again on bills aimed at funding government as blame game continues
items.description: Congressional leaders continue to blame the opposing party for the shutdown.

items.title: Offshore earthquake kills at least 69 in Philippines, officials say
items.description: A powerful 6.9-magnitude earthquake killed at least 69 people in the Philippines, officials said on Wednesday.

items.title: WATCH:  The US government has shut down for the first time in nearly 7 years
items.description: The federal government is officially shut down. ABC News' Jay O'Brien explains how we got here.

items.title: WATCH:  Carnival ride malfunctions at California school event
items.description: Riders were reportedly trapped for up to an hour after a carnival ride malfunction at a school event in Southern California. No injuries were reported...
